d intuition within that nudges us on. ) Tj296.16 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-296.16 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0961  Tc 1.0961  Tw (This, however, is not the case her) Tj138.24 0  TD -0.0894  Tc 0.8556  Tw (e. Again, it seems we are not told the whole story. The context ) Tj-174.24 -11.52  TD -0.0672  Tc 0.3472  Tw (confirms that what looked like sound strategy was, in fact, a demonstration of doubt. The people must have ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0481  Tc 1.471  Tw (had their doubts about God\222s good intentions. The people did not trust the Lord. Befo) Tj361.44 0  TD -0.1403  Tc 1.1003  Tw (re any facts were ) Tj-361.44 -11.52  TD -0.069  Tc 0.2233  Tw (gathered they had come to the conclusion: \223The LORD hates us; so he brought us out of Egypt to deliver us ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0638  Tc -0.0562  Tw (into the hands of the Amorites to destroy us.\224) Tj180 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (216) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.12  Tw ( ) Tj2.4 0  TD ( ) Tj-156.48 -11.52  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.0275  Tc 0.8125  Tw (Matthew Henry\222s Commentary) Tj127.2 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0916  Tc 0.9316  Tw ( agrees with this approach of the text. We read: \223 Orders) Tj232.32 0  TD -0.0686  Tc 0.7486  Tw ( given to ) Tj-395.52 -11.04  TD -0.0888  Tc 0.4248  Tw (send spies to search out the land of Canaan. It is here said, God directed Moses to send them \(v. 1) Tj394.08 0  TD 0.0034  Tc 0  Tw (-) Tj3.36 0  TD 0.0446  Tc -0.1646  Tw (2\), but it ) Tj-397.44 -11.52  TD -0.0569  Tc 1.3204  Tw (appears by the repetition of the story afterwards <Deut. 1:22> that the motion came originally from the ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.13  Tc 1.45  Tw (people; they came to Moses, and) Tj135.36 0  TD -0.067  Tc 0.877  Tw ( said, We will send men before us; and it was the fruit of their unbelief. ) Tj-135.36 -11.52  TD -0.0571  Tc 1.4685  Tw (They would not take God\222s word that it was a good land, and that he would, without fail, put them in ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0335  Tc 0.2655 